    <note>Chen(1) Ziqiang [3092] Because he once was the tutor of Han Tuozhou's son, he rose to be right councillor of state. All his relatives became rich. After Tuozhou was executed, he was purged, exiled to Leizhou and later died in Guangzhou (Canton). He must be a grandson of Chen(1) Yu(8) [25313], whose father moved back to Fujian. Since both he and his elder brother, Zide, are listed as grandsons of Yu(8), along with chronological logic, makes a coincidence unlikely. Fujian TZ, 149.13b. CBD, 3, 2569-2570.From Hartwell's ACTIVITY table:1200:  Apt. Jianshu Shumi yuan shi (State Council).1201:  Apt. Canzhi zhengshi concurrently Tongzhi Shumiyuan shi.1202:  Promoted to Zhi Shumi yuan shi.1203:  Apt. You chengxiang (Chief Minister).1207:  Dismissed as You chengxiang.1200:  Apt. Qianshu Shumi yuan shi (State Council)1201:  Apt. Tong Shumi yuan shi concurrently Canzhi zhengshi.1202:  Promoted to Zhi Shumi yuan shi.1203:  Apt. You chengxiang1207:  Dismissed as You chengxiang.</note>
